  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Staff Nurse",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>LC Nursing Home is a private nursing home conveniently located in Siglap, just off East Coast Road, and is easily accessible by public transport. It is nestled within a residential estate and enjoys the peaceful, clean and quiet privacy that serves the residents well.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>LC Nursing Home seeks a Staff Nurse to deliver compassionate, high-quality geriatric nursing care while collaborating effectively with the care team to enhance resident well-being.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Deliver comprehensive nursing care to geriatric residents in accordance with MOH and SNB standards to ensure safety and quality outcomes</li><li>Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams to develop and implement individualized care plans that address residents’ health needs</li><li>Monitor and assess residents’ health status regularly, identifying changes and escalating concerns promptly to support timely interventions</li><li>Demonstrate professionalism and genuine concern by providing courteous, empathetic support to residents and their families</li><li>Contribute positively to team dynamics by maintaining a cooperative attitude and supporting colleagues in daily nursing operations</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Nursing recognized by the Singapore Nursing Board</li><li>Registration as a nurse with the Singapore Nursing Board</li><li>Compliance with Ministry of Health (MOH) and Singapore Nursing Board (SNB) standards of nursing practice</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum of 3 years’ experience as a Staff Nurse, with a focus on geriatric nursing care</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
